               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390304-name-1149" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-1149" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-1149" type="surname" value="CROTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-1149" type="given" value="NAPOLEON JOHN"></interp>NAPOLEON JOHN CROTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Hope Cottage, Chapman-gardens, Hackney-road, and am a brush-maker—the prisoner had been with me about three weeks. On the 19th of February I saw him put half a dozen tooth<lb></lb>brushes into his cap, and put the cap on his head—I got a policeman, and took him to the station-house—one more brush was found on him, who duplicates for 141 brushes pawned at different pawnbrokers—they an all mine, and belonged to Mr. Patey, of Lombard-street.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390304-name-1150" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-1150" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
